From matthew liggett Subject Re engines In Paul Emery writes On the subject of the Ford in the UK used engines exstensively in their Ford Transit brings back a memory from the played in a band at the time and for something like pounds four of us bought a tranny to cart the gear around was in terrible shape cosmetically because it's last owner was a pig spent days cleaning it up and putting in a partition and more seating but 'til the day it died everytime you turned on the fan to the defroster dried pig shit came flying out the vents Back to the engine if I remember right it was a and that thing could haul we could fill it with equipment and up to people and it went like a bat out of hell of course there were no pollution controls on the engine and the gas was leaded and higher octane than we get When the mechanical fuel pump quit we put in an electric one from a Morris Minor that worked Ah fond Saab Sonnet III too I I'd like to own a squadron of tanks Paul Emery Ron Nasty The Rutles M I T Magnet Lab Cambridge Mass 'junk' collector toys R us kid antiauthoritarian and fan of frogs iguanas and other